lid, especially since it modifies protected fields directly, creating a state that's not typical for JSONPojoConvertor. I'm concerned about whether this approach offers high coverage—active call sites are useful, but the tests shouldn't feel forced or contrived. While the active class allows subclasses with public and protected fields, I think external library integration tests should ideally stick to the public API, which feels less desirable in this context.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_5MsGXOf8jLy7KxSqv3fSMSin|fc_0fc410b559300b820169f93a5a0b488192a33bcbbec9a7ecd1", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mortbay.jetty/jetty-util/6.1.26/src/test/java/org_mortbay_jetty/jetty_util/JSONPojoConvertorInnerSetterTest.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1305, "output": 2457, "cacheRead": 20992, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24754, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777941046524, "responseId": "resp_0fc410b559300b820169f93a370720819286c6f5bdbe4a20e8"}}
